Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  Notwithstanding that is the feeling of the representative of the Local Government here, he, as every man so circumstanced would most readily and anxiously do, called to his aid the Local Magistrates, and in accordance with their wishes, has authorized the organization of the inhabitants into a volunteer corp, and has entrusted to an efficient military settler the arrangement of a battery for he protection of the town, only requiring, as we think he is entitled to do, that no steps shall be taken by any <i>irresponsible</i> individuals in issuing any orders to the inhabitants unless they shall first have been submitted either to himself or some of the Magistrates of the district, and sanctioned by their approval.
